{
  "texts": [
    "\"ICL\" denotes In-Context Learning and \"CoT\" stands for Chain-of-Thoughts.",
    "• w/ CoT (least-to-most): we obtain recommendation results by prompting LLMs twice.",
    "First, LLMs are prompted to summarize the personal preference of users based on the recently interacted item sequence.",
    "Then in the second stage, we concatenate the summarized profile to the original prompt for recommendation.",
    "• w/ ICL (self instruction): we use the last interaction of the same user as the example for ICL[44]."
  ]
}